  <fr:p>Conversely, assume that every object is merely equipped with both an upshift and a downshift. That a positive object <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> has an upshift <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-004X.xml"
addr="jms-004X"
title="Uniqueness of upshifts">is a proposition</fr:link>, so we can use our assumption that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> <fr:em>merely</fr:em> has an upshift. That a negative object <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[N]]></fr:tex> has a downshift <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-004Z.xml"
addr="jms-004Z"
title="Uniqueness of downshifts">is likewise a proposition</fr:link>, so we can use our assumption that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[N]]></fr:tex> <fr:em>merely</fr:em> has a downshift.</fr:p>
